# Checklist Task Scheduling — Anchor Day Update

## What Changed

When an admin assigns a recurring task (monthly, quarterly, half-yearly, or yearly),
the system now always remembers the original day the task was set for — called the "anchor day".

Previously, if a task date fell on a holiday and was pushed forward, the next occurrence
would start from the shifted date instead of the original one. Over time, the task date
would keep drifting later and later in the month.

Now, each occurrence always starts fresh from the anchor day. The shift only ever
affects the current month — never the next one.


## How It Works

1. The admin picks a date, say the 1st of March. The anchor day is 1.

2. Every month, the system checks if the anchor day is a working day.

3. If it is — task is scheduled on that day. Done.

4. If it is a holiday or Sunday — the system looks one day back, then two days back,
   and so on, as long as it stays within the same month.

5. If going back would cross into the previous month (this only happens when the
   anchor is the 1st), the system goes forward instead — 2nd, 3rd, and so on —
   until it finds a working day.

6. The next month always resets back to the anchor day. The shift never carries over.


## Example — Anchor Day is 1st

  January 1  → Working day              → Task on 1st Jan
  February 1 → Sunday                   → Goes forward → Task on 2nd Feb
  March 1    → Working day              → Task on 1st Mar  (resets, not 2nd)
  April 1    → Holiday, 2nd also off    → Goes forward → Task on 3rd Apr
  May 1      → Working day              → Task on 1st May  (resets again)


## Example — Anchor Day is 15th

  August 15  → Independence Day         → Goes back → Task on 14th Aug
  September 15 → Working day            → Task on 15th Sep  (resets, not 14th)
  October 15 → Holiday, 14th also off   → Goes back → Task on 13th Oct
  November 15 → Working day             → Task on 15th Nov  (resets)


## Frequencies Covered

  - Monthly
  - Quarterly
  - Half-Yearly
  - Yearly

Daily, weekly, and fortnightly tasks are not affected — they advance by a fixed
number of days and do not need an anchor.


## Where the Change Was Made

  File: src/pages/admin/AssignTask.jsx

  - New function: getAnchoredMonthlyDate()
    Handles the back-then-forward logic for a given month.

  - Updated: generateTasks() and handleSubmit()
    Both the preview and the actual submit now use the new logic consistently.
